The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | GTL seals tower deal 
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      GTL seals tower deal 
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                               
	Mumbai, Jan. 14: GTL Infrastructure today reached a definitive agreement to purchase the telecom tower business of Aircel and its subsidiaries in an all-cash deal valued at Rs 8,400 crore.         
	The acquisition will make GTL Infra the worlds largest independent tower company with more than 32,500 towers across all 23 circles.         
	GTL Infra will fund this transaction through fresh equity of Rs 3,400 crore and the rest through debt. The deal is subject to regulatory approvals and is expected to be completed over the next four to five months.         
	Manoj Tirodkar, chairman of GTL Infra, said, This is a transformational deal for GTL Infra and the Indian telecom industry. It significantly enhances our scale and presence, cementing our leadership in telecom infrastructure.        
	Aircel is the fifth largest GSM mobile service provider in India.                                                                                                                                                           
